{
  "name": "Browned-Butter Protein Cookies",
  "description": "Browned-butter protein chocolate-chip cookies, makes 3. VERSION A - Thick & Gooey (molten center): tall bakery-style mounds, intentionally uneven (gooey center, firmer edges). The thick middle cooks slowest, so the edges finish before the center - that's the price of a molten center. Soft, fragile, and pale is CORRECT; these don't brown like a normal cookie. Confirm doneness by breaking one open after resting: soft/dense/moist/baked = done; wet/gummy/raw-flour = 1-2 min more. (Version B - Even & Soft-Chewy - is a derived variant that flattens + bakes lower for one consistent texture.)",
  "tags": [
    "cookie",
    "protein",
    "browned-butter",
    "chocolate-chip",
    "gooey"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 3,
    "unit": "cookies"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "s1",
        "order": 1,
        "section": "Dough",
        "instructionText": "Brown the butter: melt it in a pan over medium heat, swirling, until golden and nutty-smelling (3-4 min). Pour into a mixing bowl and let cool a couple minutes so it won't cook the egg."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s2",
        "order": 2,
        "section": "Dough",
        "instructionText": "Mix wet: whisk in the brown sugar, Splenda, whole egg, egg white, and vanilla until smooth and glossy. Don't whip air in - just combine."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s3",
        "order": 3,
        "section": "Dough",
        "instructionText": "Add dry: stir in the whey, flour, pudding mix, baking soda, and salt until a thick, scoopable dough forms, then fold in the chocolate chips. It should hold its shape, not pour. Too stiff/dry -> a splash of milk; too loose -> a bit more flour. Taste for sweetness."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s4",
        "order": 4,
        "section": "Bake - Thick & Gooey",
        "instructionText": "Chill the dough 30 minutes."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s5",
        "order": 5,
        "section": "Bake - Thick & Gooey",
        "instructionText": "Shape into 3 tall mounds - do NOT flatten."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s6",
        "order": 6,
        "section": "Bake - Thick & Gooey",
        "temperature": 350,
        "instructionText": "Bake at 350F / 175C for 9-11 minutes. Pull when the edges are set but the center still looks slightly underdone/soft. Stays pale - don't wait for golden tops."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s7",
        "order": 7,
        "section": "Finish",
        "instructionText": "Rest: leave the cookies on the hot tray 10-15 min after baking - they finish cooking from residual heat and firm up from floppy to chewy as they cool. Don't judge texture until fully cooled."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s8",
        "order": 8,
        "section": "Finish",
        "instructionText": "Fridge (optional): for a firmer, denser, chewier bite, refrigerate the cooled cookies 20-30 min or longer. Protein cookies tighten up when cold. Store leftovers in the fridge."
      }
    ],
